-- Australia, N.Z. Equities: BHP Billiton, Rio, Lynas, Westpac Bank
-- B y   E l i s a b e t h   B e h r m a n n
-- 2012-03-19T05:33:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/australia-n-z-equities-bhp-billiton-rio-lynas-westpac-bank.html
Australia ’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index (AS51) 
advanced 0.3 percent to 4,290.80 at the close of trading in
Sydney.  New Zealand (ANZ) ’s NZX 50 Index fell 0.5 percent to 3,485.97
in Wellington.  The following are among the most active shares today. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names.  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  , Australia’s biggest oil
producer, gained 1.1 percent to A$35.35. Crude prices traded
near one-week highs as investors bet the second-highest Saudi
Arabian crude output since at least 1980 signals increasing fuel
demand.  Rio Tinto Group (RIO)  , the second-biggest iron-ore
exporter, rose 1.1 percent to A$65.85 after Tropical Cyclone Lua
left its mines in Australia’s Pilbara region mostly unscathed.
BHP’s mines also escaped damage.  Lynas Corp. (LYC)   fell 1.2 percent to A$1.22 after a
report that the Malaysian government will set up a committee to
monitor the company’s rare-earths refinery in the country to
consider final approval and ongoing operation.  Westpac Banking Corp. (WBC)   rose 0.4 percent to A$21.22.
The bank leads its competitors in arranging bond sales of A$35.3
billion ($37.2 billion) since Dec. 31, as companies and foreign
borrowers lock in relative yields tumbling by the most since
September 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
